---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const routes = [
  { how: 'On foot', detail: 'From the Markapur bus stand, the temple is a short walk, and autos run the distance', dist: '\u00b7' },
  { how: 'By rail', detail: 'Markapur Road station, on the Guntakal–Vijayawada line, is within walking distance', dist: '\u00b7' },
  { how: 'From Ongole', detail: 'Buses run through the day', dist: '94 km' },
  { how: 'By road', detail: 'Markapur sits on the Amaravati–Anantapur Express Highway; approaches from Vijayawada, Guntur and Nandyal', dist: '\u00b7' },
  { how: 'Vijayawada airport', detail: 'The nearer of the two airports', dist: '227 km' },
  { how: 'Hyderabad airport', detail: 'Better connected, further away', dist: '272 km' },
];
---
<Base
  title="Getting there: Markapur, Prakasam District | Chennakesava Swamy Temple"
  description="How to reach the Sri Lakshmi Chennakesava Swami temple at Markapur by bus, rail and road, and what is known about contacting the temple office."
>
  <h1>Getting there</h1>
  <p class="page-te">మార్కాపురం, ప్రకాశం జిల్లా</p>

  <p class="lead">
    The temple stands in Markapuram town, on the banks of the Gundlakamma, in Prakasam
    District, Andhra Pradesh, <strong>523316</strong>.
  </p>

  <h3>Routes</h3>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <tbody>
        {routes.map((r) => (
          <tr>
            <td><strong>{r.how}</strong><br />
              <span style="color:var(--ink-soft); font-size:15px">{r.detail}</span></td>
            <td class="num">{r.dist}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <p style="margin-top:14px">
    <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Sri+Lakshmi+Chennakesava+Swami+Devastanam+Markapur"
       rel="noopener">Open in Google Maps →</a>
  </p>

  <svg class="kolam-rule" aria-hidden="true"><rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="url(#kolam)" /></svg>

  <h2>Contacting the temple</h2>
  <div class="note">
    <p>
      <strong>No public telephone number is listed for this temple.</strong> Not on the
      Andhra Pradesh Endowments portal, which carries a page for the temple with no
      content on it, and not on any of the sites that write about it. A devotee asked for
      the number publicly in 2017 and did not get one.
    </p>
    <p>
      Enquiries in person at the temple office. If you obtain a number that the office
      confirms, it belongs on this page.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>About this site</h2>
  <p>
    It is built and maintained by devotees. It is not the temple's official site, it is
    not run by the Endowments Department, and nothing here has been confirmed by either.
    Timings, festival dates and the history are compiled from public sources, which
    disagree with one another more often than you would expect.
  </p>
  <p>
    Where sources conflict, this site publishes the most cautious reading: the earliest
    closing time, no seva prices, no dates for the sun phenomenon. A visitor who arrives
    to find the temple open an hour later than we said has lost nothing. The reverse costs
    somebody a journey.
  </p>
</Base>
